07May, here's my plotline idea for the competiton. I never got to write it though
07So might as well just say it.
07Since it was a love-story, I assumed that Lugia and Articuno would get married at one point -- with Lugia wanting to porpose to her under the mistletoe (to involve the theme, y'know?) -- but they'd have to find it. Seems fine so far... Right.
07
07I would've revealed this in the story if I'd ever gotten that far -- Ho-oh somehow getting the bright idea that he wanted Articuno for himself. After all, Lugia was less of a bird than he was, although he'd have done his fair share of bribery and convincing to get Lugia to agree to this... Giving up Arti and letting him have her, that is.
07And to cover it up, Lugia had Zapdos and Moltres make this stew thing that they would apply to the leaves of the mistletoe, which of course, again, to include the theme, could only be found in one place. That way, Lugia would look innocent.
07
07When Lugia and Articuno went to find the mistletoe, she wouldn't suspect much, with Lugia encouraging her to pick it up -- and she'd have to do this with her beak, as there's really no other effective way of plucking a plant for a bird.
